The paper discusses the challenges faced by web archivists in preserving digital history due to the evolving web technologies. This topic falls under the domain of digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR) as web archivists work to preserve and retrieve web pages. The paper also discusses the technical aspects of web archiving, which aligns with the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the accessibility of web pages, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper focuses on the archivability of web pages, which is directly related to web technologies (cs.WEB).
